To install AWS CLI , open powershell as admin : 
choco install awscli -y
and in aws console, create IAM user and access key

//Configure it
pari9@Pari MINGW64 ~
$ aws --version
aws-cli/2.27.35 Python/3.13.3 Windows/11 exe/AMD64

pari9@Pari MINGW64 ~
$ aws configure
AWS Access Key ID [****************MIEN]: 
AWS Secret Access Key [****************DDlO]: 
Default region name [us-east-1]: us-east-1
Default output format [None]: json

ls ~/.aws/
config  credentials
In config you should have region and output 
In credentials you should have access key id and pass

aws sts get-caller-identity //User details 
aws ec2 describe-instances








